div.p:
OH! from the rock of the hill;
from the top of the mountain of winds,
ſpeak ye ghoſts of the dead! ſpeak,
and I will not be afraid.—Whither
are ye gone to reſt? In what cave of
the hill ſhall I find you?

RISE, Cuchulaid, riſe! I ſee the ſhips
of Garve. Many are the foe, Cuchulaid;
many the ſons of Lochlyn.
